- Running out of IPv4 addresses
	- 2^32 addresses available
	- NAT and Private IPs have helped conserve the use of IPv4

IPv6:
	- 128 bits
	- 32 Hexedecimal Characters
		- Divided into 8 groups of 4

Shortening/Abbreviating IPV6 Addresses:
	- Leading 0s can be removed
	- Consecutive quartets of all 0s can be replaced with a double colon
		- Can only be abbreviated once in a given addresses
	- 
